==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wright
<hw>Wright</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>wrighte</ets>, <ets>writhe</ets>, AS. <ets>wyrtha</ets>, fr.
<ets>wyrcean</ets> to work. ⟦root⟧145. See <er>Work</er>.]</ety>
<def>One who is engaged in a mechanical or manufacturing business; an
artificer; a workman; a manufacturer; a mechanic; esp., a worker in
wood; -- now chiefly used in compounds, as in mill<xex>wright</xex>,
wheel<xex>wright</xex>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He was a well good <qex>wright</qex>, a carpenter.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wrightine</ent>⟦br⟧
